RoleDescription:
Your contribution to something big:- Mechanical development of new products (Sensors) and defining the specifications and technical documentation of those products;
- Responsible for complete product life cycle: Customer iteration, requirements evaluation, product development, engineering change requests, bill of materials, customer change requests;
- Creation of 3D design solutions, using CAD modelling tools and creation of 2D drawings by using existing specifications inside project, as well as creation of specifications for suppliers and production;
- Simultaneous engineering with all the parties involved in the development of new products (project lead, production, process engineering, suppliers, sample shop,...);
- Participation and technical lead during supplier selection and sourcing process for parts;
- Follow-up of supplier processes, such as tool creation, to reach maturity before release for mass production;
- Interface to other development sites and communication to Project Manager;
- Conduct investigations and root cause analysis of concept problems and implement corrective measures;
- Participation in problem solving teams, including participants from other departments such as Purchase, Quality, Suppliers;
- Analyze costs and benchmarking of state-of-the-art technology.What distinguishes you:- Mechanical/Polymer Engineer with experience in Automotive Development;
- Independent working attitude, ability to work inside teams from engineering, production, quality, suppliers (national and international);
- Good Experience in simulation tools with finite element (FEM) for structural analysis;
- Analytic mindset, willing to perform independently detailed technical investigations, both practical and theoretical;
- Knowledge in Design and Production of injections molded Plastic / Metal parts and Sheet Metal Parts;
- Excellent knowledge in Part Dimensioning and GDT;
- Excellent knowledge in CAD (NX or CREO) in 2D and 3D modules;
- Knowledge in Quality and Problem Solving Methods;
- Excellent communication skills towards management, suppliers and customers;
- Secure in technical documentations and presentations;
- Good English language skills;
- Experience in creating and presenting technical documentations.Work #LikeABosch includes: Flexible work conditions Hybrid work system Exchange with colleagues around the world Health insurance and medical office on site (psychology and general clinic) Training opportunities (p.e., technical training, foreign languages training) &amp; certifications Opportunities for career progression and continuous professional development Access to great discounts in partnerships and Bosch products Sports and health related activities Great access to public transports Free transport from Porto Flexible benefits platform Free parking lot Canteen Success stories don t just happen. They are made...Make it happen! We are looking forward to your application!
